  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DanChurchAid&apos;s activities in South Sudan, Ethiopia, Uganda and Kenya, 2014</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">: The project supported 70,508 conflict affected people in South Sudan, Ethiopia, Uganda and Kenya. 22,410 conflict affected people in South Sudan and in Uganda are provided with cash grants for food purchases and/or vegetable seeds in order to improve food security for vulnerable families. 85.000 newly arrived South Sudanese refugees who have fled to Ethiopia and Uganda were supported with basic relief items (soap, jerry cans cooking pots, plastic sheets etc.). Finally, a water tank was constructed in a new section of refugee camp, Kakuma in Kenya. The tank improved access to water for 5,500 South Sudanese refugees in the Kakuma Refugee Camp in Kenya, ensuring 20 liters of water per person as recommended by UNHCR.</narrative>
  </description>
